The paper deals with object localization, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves transferring knowledge from a source set to a target set, which is a common approach in transfer learning (cs.LG). The authors also use similarity and co-occurrence relations between classes, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves generating segmentation maps, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the authors use a multiple instance learning framework, which is a common approach in natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
